Sharon Rowlands








LeadershipSharon RowlandsSharon Rowlands has been a Director of Pega since April  2016.
Ms. Rowlands was named CEO of ReachLocal, an internet-based  provider of advertising and marketing services, in April 2014. Ms. Rowlands has  more than 20 years' experience leading complex, multi-billion dollar business  services and software companies serving enterprise customers. From 2011 to  2013, she was CEO of Altegrity, which she transformed from a holding company  into three independent business units, each with its own growth strategy. From  2008 to 2011 Ms. Rowlands was CEO of Penton Media, and prior to that she was  with Thomson Financial. During her more than ten-year tenure at Thomson, she  held a variety of executive-level positions, including President and CEO from  2005 to 2008 and established the company as one of the most innovative partners  to the global financial community. Previously, Ms. Rowlands held executive  leadership roles at Financial Times Information (now Interactive Data Pricing  and Reference Data, Inc.). She was previously a Member of the Board of  Directors of Constant Contact (Nasdaq: CTCT) and served on the Board of  Directors for Automatic Data Processing, Inc. (Nasdaq: ADP) from 2008 to 2011.  She currently serves on the Board of Directors for Local Search Association,  the largest trade organization of companies engaged in local advertising and  marketing.
Ms. Rowlands received her Postgraduate  Certificate of Education from Goldsmiths, University of London and her Bachelor  of Arts in History from the University of Newcastle, Newcastle-Upon-Tyne.<< Back to all











 















